prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Cameras monitor roads with high traffic levels to facilitate traffic signals.",
      "evidence_quote": "Cameras to monitor the roads with high traffic levels in order to facilitate the traffic signal."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Helmet and seat belt detection using image processing warns drivers.",
      "evidence_quote": "Helmet and seat belt detection using image processing to warn the drivers."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Details of driver are submitted to traffic police via number plate when violating law more than two times.",
      "evidence_quote": "Details of the driver are submitted to the traffic police, when he/she violates the law more than two times via the number plate which is captured by cameras."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Street lights operate based on population density at night to save electricity.",
      "evidence_quote": "Street lights are operated based on the population density on road at night, thereby saving electricity."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "License is cancelled as penalty for violating law.",
      "evidence_quote": "License will be cancelled as penalty, if the law is violated."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Details of driver are passed to successive signals on account of speeding.",
      "evidence_quote": "Details of the driver will be passed on to successive signals on account of speeding."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Automated traffic lights regulate traffic flow to avoid congestions.",
      "evidence_quote": "Automated traffic lights regulate the traffic flow in order to avoid congestions"
    }
  ]
}

